: "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It seems to be an issue with `literal`s vs `expr`s in macro rules, in particular for the unary operation `-`.\r\n\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[macro_export]\r\nmacro_rules! test {\r\n    ($a:literal) => { $a };\r\n    ($a:expr) => { $a };\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn func() {\r\n    let a = test!(0);\r\n    let b = test!(a);\r\n    let c = test!(-a);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: No errors and that the second branch would be used for the assignment of both `b` and `c`.\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: I got the following error:\r\n```\r\nerror: unexpected token: `a`\r\n   --> src/gate.rs:144:20\r\n    |\r\n137 |     ($a:literal) => { $a };\r\n    |      ---------- while parsing argument for this `literal` macro fragment\r\n...\r\n144 |     let c = test!(-a);\r\n    |     \r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.52.0-nightly (3a5d45f68 2021-03-09)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 3a5d45f68cadc8fff4fbb557780f92b403b19c19\r\ncommit-date: 2021-03-09\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.52.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 12.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n```\r\n   Compiling rs-bug v0.1.0 (/home/axel/tmp/rs-bug)\r\nerror: unexpected token: `a`\r\n  --> src/main.rs:10:20\r\n   |\r\n3  |     ($a:literal) => { $a };\r\n   |      ---------- while parsing argument for this `literal` macro fragment\r\n...\r\n10 |     let c = test!(-a);\r\n   |                    ^\r\n\r\nerror: aborting due to previous error\r\n\r\nerror: could not compile `rs-bug`\r\n\r\nTo learn more, run the command again with --verbose. \r\n```\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "jonas-schievink", "id": 1786438, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODY0Mzg=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1786438?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonas-schievink", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonas-schievink", "followers_u